The paper deals with computational complexity of graph labeling problems, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The use of neighborhood diversity and clique width as parameters suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Graph Theory (cs.GT). Finally, the mention of Channel Assignment problems suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
